cs.DC, cs.CE, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.SE

This paper discusses the development and deployment of scientific computing applications in the cloud, which involves distributed computing and system architecture. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses the challenges and opportunities in the future development of cloud-based eScience services, which involves software engineering and cybersecurity. Therefore, cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also a likely category. Other possible categories include cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), cs.CY (Computers and Society), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as they are related to the applications and implications of cloud-based eScience services.
